12/05/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The eighth South-East European Co-operation Process (SEECP) summit in Bucharest ended Wednesday (11 May) with a joint declaration vowing increased regional co-operation on behalf of EU integration. The declaration, signed by the heads of SEECP states -- Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Greece, Macedonia, Romania, Serbia-Montenegro and Turkey -- voiced commitment to improving security in the region, as well as collaborating in EU-backed initiatives. 
During the summit, Romanian President Traian Basescu asked his counterparts to support efforts to win the release of three Romanian journalists held hostage in Iraq. (Nine o'clock, Rompres, Anadolu Agency, Fena, AP, Reuters - 11/05/05)
